Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defendant Onae A Butler in court, in custody, with attorney Nicholas Martinez.   Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a no contest plea to the charge. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

2 1/2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT  (consecutive)
  -  1 1/2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  1 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S); concurrent

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  any victims
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
 
COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DRGOD SURCHARGE:  $10.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  6 months:  1st 2 months straight time, 2nd 2 months with huber and the last 2 months STAYED to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Expungement is denied.
Probation may be transferred to Milwaukee County
Jail time may be transferred to Milwaukee County will no electronic monitoring 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
